# {{PROJECT_NAME}} — Design Language & Visual Consistency

Every LWC in this portal must visually match the established design language defined by the reference components `{{REFERENCE_LWC_A}}` and `{{REFERENCE_LWC_B}}`. Match these; do not invent new chrome.

## 1. Design tokens (declare at `:host`)
```css
:host {
    --{{PREFIX}}-font-family:         '{{FONT_FAMILY}}';        /* e.g. 'Open Sans' */
    --{{PREFIX}}-color-primary:       {{PRIMARY_HEX}};          /* brand color */
    --{{PREFIX}}-color-primary-light: {{PRIMARY_LIGHT_HEX}};    /* light tint */
}
```
All text uses `font-family: var(--{{PREFIX}}-font-family)`. All brand backgrounds reference the token, never a hardcoded hex — single point of change if the palette updates.

## 2. Status pattern (be consistent everywhere)
- **Semantic pills:** light tinted background + dark same-family text + 1px border (SLDS badge pattern). NOT solid saturated fill with white text.
- **Left-border accents:** 3–4px solid left border, color matched to status/type. Use on alert cards and calendar/list tiles.

## 3. Card structure
- Outer wrapper: `slds-card {{PREFIX}}-outer-card` (e.g. `border-radius: 1rem`).
- Header bar: branded background token, white bold header text.
- AI / generated content: a distinct inset card (left-border accent + light tint + optional `backdrop-filter: blur()`), a sparkle icon (`utility:sparkles`), a caps label, and an italic "Generated by AI on {datetime}" footnote.

## 4. Shadow-DOM caveat
If a third-party library (e.g. a calendar) renders elements **outside** the LWC shadow DOM, class-based custom properties do not pierce through. Set the property via JS (`el.style.setProperty('--token', value)`), consistent with how inline `backgroundColor`/`color` are already applied.

## 5. LWC meta
```xml
<apiVersion>{{API_VERSION}}</apiVersion>
<isExposed>true</isExposed>
<targets>
    <target>lightningCommunity__Default</target>
    <target>lightningCommunity__Page</target>
</targets>
```

